20data-toc-label%3D%5C%2230-Year%20Rates%5C%22%3E30-Year%20Mortgage%20Rates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAverage%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2F30-year-mortgage-rates%5C%22%3E30-year%20mortgage%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20around%206.30%25%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fwhat-is-zillow%5C%22%3EZillow%3C%2Fa%3E%20data.%20This%20rate%20was%206.56%25%20in%20November.%20Rates%20rose%20substantially%20last%20month%2C%20though%20they're%20a%20bit%20lower%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2030-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgage%20is%20the%20most%20popular%20home%20loan.%20With%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Ftypes-of-mortgage-loans%5C%22%3Etype%20of%20mortgage%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you'll%20pay%20back%20what%20you%20borrowed%20over%2030%20years%2C%20and%20your%20interest%20rate%20won't%20change%20for%20the%20life%20of%20the%20loan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lengthy%2030-year%20term%20allows%20you%20to%20spread%20out%20your%20payments%20over%20a%20long%20period%20of%20time%2C%20meaning%20you%20can%20keep%20your%20monthly%20payments%20lower%20and%20more%20manageable.%20The%20trade-off%20is%20that%20you'll%20have%20a%20higher%20rate%20than%20you%20would%20with%20shorter%20terms%2C%20like%20a%2015-year%20mortgage.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%2215-Year%20Rates%5C%22%3E15-Year%20Mortgage%20Rates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAverage%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2F15-year-mortgage-rates%5C%22%3E15-year%20mortgage%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20hovering%20in%20the%20high%205%25%20range%2C%20according%20to%20Zillow%20data.%20In%20November%2C%2015-year%20rates%20averaged%205.92%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20the%20predictability%20that%20comes%20with%20a%20fixed%20rate%20but%20are%20looking%20to%20spend%20less%20on%20interest%20over%20the%20life%20of%20your%20loan%2C%20a%2015-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgage%20might%20be%20a%20good%20fit%20for%20you.%20Because%20these%20terms%20are%20shorter%20and%20have%20lower%20rates%20than%2030-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgages%2C%20you%20could%20potentially%20save%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20in%20interest.%20However%2C%20you'll%20have%20a%20higher%20monthly%20payment%20than%20you%20would%20with%20a%20longer%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22ARM%20Rates%5C%22%3EARM%20Rates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERates%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fadjustable-rate-mortgage%5C%22%3Eadjustable-rate%20mortgages%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20higher%20than%20fixed%20rates%20recently.%20Last%20month%2C%20the%20average%20mortgage%20rate%20for%20a%207%2F1%20ARM%20was%206.82%25%2C%20while%20the%20average%20rate%20for%20a%205%2F1%20ARM%20was%206.83%25%2C%20according%20to%20Zillow%20data.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20get%20an%20ARM%2C%20you'll%20have%20a%20fixed%20mortgage%20rate%20for%20a%20certain%20period%20of%20time%2C%20after%20which%20your%20rate%20will%20adjust%20periodically.%20On%20a%207%2F1%20ARM%2C%20for%20example%2C%20your%20rate%20will%20stay%20fixed%20for%20seven%20years%2C%20and%20then%20adjust%20once%20a%20year%20after%20that%20until%20you%20pay%20off%20the%20loan%20or%20refinance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Farm-rates-today%5C%22%3EARM%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20often%20(but%20not%20always)%20lower%20than%20their%20fixed-rate%20counterparts%2C%20making%20an%20ARM%20a%20good%20deal%20if%20you're%20looking%20to%20save%20on%20your%20monthly%20mortgage%20payment.%20But%20the%20risk%20with%20an%20ARM%20is%20that%20your%20monthly%20payment%20could%20increase%20if%20rates%20are%20up%20when%20your%20rate%20starts%20adjusting.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22FHA%20Interest%20Rates%5C%22%3EFHA%20Interest%20Rates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Ffha-interest-rates%5C%22%3EFHA%20interest%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%205.41%25%20last%20month%2C%20and%20they're%20a%20bit%20higher%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Ffha-loan%5C%22%3EFHA%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20insured%20by%20the%20Federal%20Housing%20Administration.%20This%20federal%20backing%20allows%20lenders%20to%20work%20with%20borrowers%20with%20lower%20credit%20scores%20and%20less%20money%20for%20a%20down%20payment%2C%20making%20these%20loans%20a%20good%20option%20for%20low-income%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fbest-mortgage-lenders-first-time-buyers%5C%22%3Efirst-time%20homebuyers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20also%20typically%20have%20lower%20rates%20compared%20to%20conventional%20mortgages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20get%20an%20FHA%20loan%2C%20you'll%20need%20a%20credit%20score%20of%20at%20least%20580%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fhow-much-down-payment-for-a-house%5C%22%3Edown%20payment%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%203.5%25.%20If%20you%20can%20afford%20to%20put%2010%25%20down%20on%20a%20house%2C%20you%20could%20qualify%20for%20an%20FHA%20loan%20with%20a%20score%20down%20to%20500%2C%20though%20not%20all%20lenders%20offer%20this%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22VA%20Mortgage%20Rates%5C%22%3EVA%20Mortgage%20Rates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fcurrent-va-mortgage-rates%5C%22%3ECurrent%20VA%20mortgage%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20in%20the%20mid-5%25%20range%2C%20according%20to%20Zillow%20data.%20Last%20month%2C%20VA%20rates%20averaged%205.97%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fva-loans%5C%22%3EVA%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20available%20to%20veterans%20and%20military%20members%20who%20meet%20minimum%20service%20requirements.%20They're%20backed%20by%20the%20Department%20of%20Veterans%20Affairs%2C%20and%20require%20no%20down%20payment%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fpmi-private-mortgage-insurance%5C%22%3Emortgage%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Refinance%20Rates%5C%22%3EMortgage%20Refinance%20Rates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fcurrent-mortgage-refinance-rates%5C%22%3ERefinance%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20holding%20steady.%20Last%20month%2C%2030-year%20refinance%20rates%20averaged%206.62%25%2C%20while%2015-year%20refinance%20rates%20were%20around%205.96%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EHow%20Much%20Do%20Mortgage%20Rates%20Need%20to%20Drop%20to%20Refinance%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20wondering%20if%20you%20should%20refinance%20now%2C%20you'll%20need%20to%20crunch%20the%20numbers%20to%20see%20if%20it%20makes%20sense.%20Some%20experts%20advise%20only%20refinancing%20if%20you%20can%20reduce%20your%20rate%20by%20a%20percentage%20point%20or%20more%2C%20but%20it%20really%20comes%20down%20to%20whether%20it%20works%20for%20your%20individual%20circumstances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20can%20save%20enough%20each%20month%20by%20refinancing%20that%20you%20can%20recoup%20your%20costs%20in%20a%20reasonable%20amount%20of%20time%2C%20it%20might%20be%20worth%20it.%20You%20can%20calculate%20this%20by%20dividing%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fwhat-are-mortgage-closing-costs%5C%22%3Eclosing%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20amount%20you're%20saving%20on%20your%20monthly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Faverage-mortgage-payment%5C%22%3Emortgage%20payment%3C%2Fa%3E.%20So%2C%20if%20you%20paid%20%2