Rates%3F%5C%22%3EHow%20Does%20the%20Fed%20Affect%20Mortgage%20Rates%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20aggressively%20raised%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-the-federal-funds-rate%5C%22%3Efederal%20funds%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202022%20and%202023%20to%20slow%20economic%20growth%20and%20get%20inflation%20under%20control.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20mortgage%20rates%20spiked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20aren't%20directly%20impacted%20by%20changes%20to%20the%20federal%20funds%20rate%2C%20but%20they%20often%20trend%20up%20or%20down%20ahead%20of%20Fed%20moves.%20This%20is%20because%20mortgage%20rates%20change%20based%20on%20investor%20demand%20for%20mortgage-backed%20securities%2C%20and%20this%20demand%20is%20often%20impacted%20by%20how%20investors%20expect%20Fed%20hikes%20to%20affect%20the%20broader%20economy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20September%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-cuts-interest-rates-how-much-september-fomc-powell-inflation-2024-9%5C%22%3Ethe%20Fed%20started%20lowering%20its%20benchmark%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20it%20cut%20rates%20again%20in%20November.%20Mortgage%20rates%20are%20still%20elevated%2C%20but%20over%20time%20they%20should%20ease%20as%20the%20Fed%20lowers%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Mortgage%20Rate%20Predictions%202025%5C%22%3EMortgage%20Rate%20Predictions%202025%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20increased%20last%20month%2C%20but%20they're%20expected%20to%20drop%20next%20year%20as%20the%20Fed%20lowers%20its%20benchmark%20rate%20and%20inflation%20cools.%20However%2C%20that%20forecast%20could%20change%20depending%20on%20how%20the%20economy%20evolves%20in%202025.%20Right%20now%2C%20the%20Fed%20is%20poised%20to%20achieve%20a%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bsoft%20landing%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20it%20successfully%20brings%20inflation%20back%20down%20to%20its%202%25%20target%20without%20sparking%20an%20economic%20downturn.%20I