%20to%20happen%20to%20me.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20was%20fortuitous%20since%20I%20needed%20to%20take%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearly-retirement-not-worth-it-dad-sacrificed-frugal-died-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20early%20retirement%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20from%20my%20job%20as%20a%20hospital%20executive%20after%20my%20retina%20detached%20and%20I%20lost%20sight%20in%20my%20right%20eye.%20No%20one%20wants%20a%20one-eyed%20pharmacist.%20Luckily%2C%20my%20financial%20situation%20meant%20I%20was%20comfortable%20leaving%20that%20job%20at%2038.%20I%20continued%20to%20invest%20and%20accrue%20wealth%20and%20was%20a%20millionaire%20the%20next%20year.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224ab7e173-07c8-4ef3-9b0a-ebf286d11c52%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20skip%20drinks%20at%20restaurants%20but%20travel%20internationally%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthis-woman-says-extreme-frugality-changed-her-life-how-she-saves-money-2018-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Elive%20frugally%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20helped%20me%20become%20a%20millionaire.%20I%20focused%20on%20getting%20rid%20of%20or%20avoiding%20consumer%20debt%20and%20started%20investing%20early.%20I%20even%20invested%20a%20portion%20of%20my%20student%20loans%20after%20keeping%20my%20cost%20of%20living%20low.%20I%20wouldn't%20recommend%20that%2C%20but%20it%20worked%20for%20me.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20still%20live%20by%20those%20principles.%20We're%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-shares-benefits-biking-around-with-kids-instead-of-driving-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eone-car%20family%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20and%20that%20car%20is%20a%202016%20Honda%20Accord.%20We%20rarely%20eat%20out%2C%20and%20we%20don't%20order%20alcohol%20or%20sodas%20when%20we%20do.%20These%20things%20aren't%20important%20to%20our%20family%2C%20so%20we%20don't%20spend%20on%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInstead%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-travelers-splurge-on-for-vacation-trends-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewe%20splurge%20on%20the%20things%20that%20have%20real%20value%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20us%2C%20including%20travel.%20We%20love%20to%20travel%20internationally%20as%20a%20family.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2267d6c5f5-bcb7-48e7-a9b8-3f89b7dcf320%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20trip%20to%20the%20DMV%20made%20me%20realize%20I%20can't%20always%20control%20my%20kid's%20expectations%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20kids%20range%20in%20age%20from%208%20to%2020.%20We've%20helped%20the%20two%20oldest%20buy%20cars%20by%20matching%20the%20amount%20that%20they%20saved.%20My%20oldest%20bought%20a%202008%20Nissan%20Altima%20for%20her%20first%20car.%20She%20was%20so%20proud%20of%20researching%20the%20car%20and%20negotiating%20the%20sale%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20showing%20her%20a%20valuable%20life%20lesson.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThen%2C%20we%20got%20to%20the%20DMV%20to%20register%20the%20car.%20My%20daughter%20looked%20around%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWhere's%20the%20fast%20pass%20line%3F%26quot%3B%20Because%20our%20family%20values%20experiences%2C%20we're%20always%20willing%20to%20spend%20on%20skipping%20the%20line%2C%20by%20paying%20for%20tools%20like%20TSA%20Pre-Check.%20That%20was%20an%20aha%20moment.%20No%20matter%20how%20intentional%20I%20am%20with%20raising%20the%20kids%20to%20not%20be%20entitled%2C%20they're%20only%20going%20to%20know%20what%20they're%20used%20to.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221caac615-c4de-413c-a04a-296e80afa377%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20give%20our%20kids%20a%20%241%2C500%20launching%20bonus%2C%20then%20they're%20on%20their%20own%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20two%20oldest%20(18%20and%2020)%20have%20moved%20out%20of%20the%20house%20because%20it's%20important%20to%20me%20that%20they%20are%20independent.%20There%20are%20things%20you%20won't%20learn%20until%20you're%20living%20on%20your%20own.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20the%20kids%20get%20ready%20to%20move%20out%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20ask%20them%20to%20prepare%20a%20budget.%20Once%20we%20see%20that%2C%20we%20give%20them%20a%20one-time%20%241%2C500%20launch%20payment%20to%20help%20them%20get%20started.%20After%20that%2C%20they're%20100%25%20on%20their%20own.%20Money%20is%20spent%20differently%20when%20it's%20yours.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227497913b-d6d3-4f43-8c63-7ac0f6d29c0b%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWe're%20not%20paying%20for%20college%20up%20front%2C%20but%20we%20will%20help%20with%20loans%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20parents%20had%20a%20policy%20that%20I'd%20always%20have%20food%20and%20a%20roof%20over%20my%20head.%20In%20line%20with%20that%2C%20they%20paid%20for%20my%20room%20and%20board%20in%20college%20while%20I%20covered%20tuition.%20I%20left%20school%20with%20minimal%20loans%20and%20a%20degree%20in%20pharmacy%20that%20led%20me%20to%20a%20lucrative%20career.%20That's%20contributed%20to%20my%20financial%20success.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStill%2C%20I've%20taken%20a%20different%20approach%20with%20my%20kids%2C%20and%20we're%20not%20paying%20for%20their%20college%20up%20front.%20However%2C%20we%20still%20have%20a%20plan%20to%20help%20them.%20When%20they%20graduate%2C%20we'll%20either%20pay%20off%20their%20student%20loans%20or%20help%20with%20a%20down%20payment%20on%20a%20house.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20don't%20have%20a%20set%20amount%20for%20this%20or%20other%20financial%20decisions%20regarding%20the%20kids.%20I%20don't%20think%20parenting%20always%20needs%20to%20be%20even%20to%20be%20fair.%20