y%20to%20comprehend%20them.%20In%202024%20alone%2C%20SABIA%20has%20extended%20its%20reach%20to%20over%2030%2C000%20children%20across%20175%20schools.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EBuilding%20a%20community%20of%20readers%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20UPSC%20aspirant%20and%20a%20voracious%20reader%2C%20Srishti%20was%20heavily%20invested%20in%20volunteer%20work.%20Recalling%20a%20conversation%20she%20had%20with%20a%20friend%20who%20had%20taken%20her%20house-help%E2%80%99s%20son%20to%20be%20admitted%20to%20a%20school%20under%20the%20Right%20to%20Education%20Act%2C%20Srishti%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CMy%20friend%20mentioned%20that%20the%20children%20in%20that%20government%20school%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20library.%20They%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20place%20to%20read!%20That%20really%20stuck%20with%20me.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20product%20of%20a%20privileged%20education%20system%20where%20access%20to%20libraries%20was%20a%20given%2C%20many%20of%20us%20fail%20to%20consider%20that%20such%20a%20fundamental%20resource%20is%20missing%20for%20so%20many%20children.%20Srishti%20soon%20started%20a%20Facebook%20page%2C%20then%20moved%20to%20Instagram%20and%20formed%20a%20strong%20%E2%80%98Bookstagram%E2%80%99%20community%2C%20where%20she%20rallied%20friends%20and%20family%20to%20donate%20books.%20It%20was%20here%20that%20they%20found%20a%20group%20of%20people%20who%20really%20understood%20and%20empathised%20with%20the%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%5Cn%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20it%20grew%20into%20a%20full-fledged%20initiative%20that%20now%20includes%20a%20library%20development%20programme%20for%20rural%20and%20remote%20schools%2C%20a%20teacher%20training%20programme%2C%20book%20fairs%2C%20and%20donation%20drives.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20holistic%20approach%20to%20education%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20sur